fields.bio: To me, my cello lesson is half an hour of peace. When I play, it feels like I have transported to a different universe. In the future I want to be a famous cellist like Sheku Kanneh-Mason
Brass specialising in French Horn (beginner to advanced), Music Theory, Piano (beginners only) and Aural Preparation (Grade 1-6).

Ed is a recent graduate from the Birmingham Conservatoire.Ed has a wide variety of performance experience around the UK (Big bands, Jazz Combos, Show bands. pop/funk/reggae bands, Punjabi/Bollywood bands). He is an encouraging and a very enthusiastic approachable musician to work with Lessons are tailored to suit the needs of each individual student covering areas: instrumental technique, reading, jazz harmony and improvisation.

I have a wealth of experience as a trumpeter, playing in orchestras, brass ensembles, stage bands and as a soloist. I was a member of the National Youth Orchestra of GB, under the baton of Mark Elder and Richard Hickox, and was principal trumpet of orchestras at Cambridge and Warwick universities.

I have a wealth of experience as a trumpeter, playing in orchestras, brass ensembles, stage bands and as a soloist. I was a member of the National Youth Orchestra of GB, under the baton of Mark Elder and Richard Hickox, and was principal trumpet of orchestras at Cambridge and Warwick universities.
I have recently completed my MMUS at Newcastle University and play Clarinet, saxophone and beginners piano.All Newcastle areas coveredwith preference to teach in student's homes.

I recently graduated from Birmingham Conservatoire.I am looking for pupils who are interested in learning piano, oboe, bassoon, flute, clarinet or music theory. I have plenty of experience teaching children of varying abilities, but am happy to also teach adult learners. I have a full and clear CRB.

I'm passionate about music and I love to impart my knowledge. I have a natural empathy with pupils and love to find different ways to explain, approach and show solutions. Every student is different and has individual needs, and I adapt accordingly. Lessons have to be enjoyable for both of us. I'm a very committed teacher and I expect similar commitment in return, but my feet are firmly on the ground and I understand the many other pulls that students face these days.
Teach Clarinet, Saxophone and Recorder. Studying at the Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama. Online lessons available.

Whether you're just starting and want to learn to strum along to your first song in a relaxed and friendly environment or you've being playing for a while and want know how to improve your ability to improvise over your favourite tunes. Get in touch to discuss your options.

Lessons are taught in a friendly and relaxed environment.Students have the option to do grades or they can learn just for fun.Lessons can take place on Zoom/Skype or I can travel to your home for an extra cost (variable on location).I have an enhanced DBS (CRB) certificate.For more information go to www.cathbayleymusic.co.uk

Hi there! Thank you for visiting my teaching profile. I am a recent postgraduate of Music from the University of York and a freelance musician and teacher living in York. I have been teaching on various instruments for three years from ages 5-50 and really enjoy teaching a diverse range of pupils.I like to make my lessons fun and engaging, for example playing a couple of duets together, looking at tone colours, suggesting a range of styles, to help keep it varied.

I am a 2nd year music student at Huddersfield specialising in performance (oboe). I deliver lessons during university tearm time. I am registered with ABRSM so I am able to enter students for graded exams if they so wish.I also can teach music theory up to Grade 5 level.I do not have a car and so lessons are to be held at my house unless the students house is withing 45 minutes walking distance.
Happy to travel to students houses for lessons.

I am currenlty studying at Leeds Conservatoire and have been playing harp since I was 6. I am passionate about demonstrating the beauty of this instrument with aspiring young musicians. Fully DBS checked and available for online or face to face lessons in central Leeds. All ages and abilities catered for..

I am an enthusastic and approachable double bass player and teacher living in Leeds. Classically trained, I have a first class honours degree in Music majoring in solo classical performance. I am also widely experienced in jazz and folk styles, playing regularly with classical ensembles and in an alternative folk band, Hunting Bears.

My main love in music is Jazz, however I also teach many other genres such as Blues, Pop, Latin, Funk and Rock music and am happy to teach any level of musician from complete beginner to someone who wants to expand their playing into different styles or to have a deeper knowledge of the style they currently love to play.

Hello everyone! I am an experienced teacher offering bespoke lessons in piano and popular singing: each lesson is designed for each individual student, according to the student's needs and interests, using a variety of teaching strategies to enhance the learning experience. I work hard to ensure that my students are happy, motivated and learning at all times! I enjoy teaching all ages and abilities.

The skills I teach include good technique, reading and writing drum and tuned notation and playing in numerous different styles. All of these vital skills can be transferred from the drum kit to a djembé, conga or kitchen table. If you can hit it, scrape it or shake it, it becomes a percussion instrument!Since I had my first drum lesson, at 10 years old, I've never stopped learning and I aspire to pass my knowledge on to others.

I am John Hutchinson, a Professional Violinist and Violin Teacher based in London. I represent the youngest member of a family spanning three generations of musicians.With over a decade of teaching experience, I have tutored students from age 3 to adults with a mix of ability from beginners to post diploma. I now have a large studio drawing in students from around the UK and Asia with lessons taking in place in person and via Zoom.Currently I am teaching at The Royal Ballet School.

I usually teach student aged over 7 and happy to make them prepare for ABRSM exams or play as accompanist to help them to improve their abilities.In some case happy to travel at your place for your convenience. I successfully completed The World of the String Quartet course provided by Curtis Institute of Music in the US and achieved the certificate of Fundamentals of Rehearsing Music Ensembles in university of North Carolina as well as a few more courses.

My aim as a teacher is to encourage my students whilst creating a love for music-making!I have experience teaching at various levels, whether it is beginner/intermediate/amateur or advanced level.I can assist with ABRSM Practical Exams on Violin, Viola and Piano (the latter up to Grade 5), as well as Theory (up to Grade 5). I am fully DBS checked.

Experienced international performer and teacher, I have given live broadcasts on both national TV and Radio.Students of all ages and abilities welcome, feel free to call and discuss lessons.FREE consultation lesson.DBS checked.

My teaching experience includes the coaching and conducting of percussion ensembles and I have given private lessons on all types of percussion including drum kit. I have also taught the theory of music and have given tuition for aural exams. I can offer a wide variety of percussion tuition including drum kit, Latin percussion and orchestral playing.I have recently completed my postgraduate studies at Trinity Laban Conservatoire and did my undergradat the RAM.

My name is Amy and I'm a graduate of the Royal Northern College of Music where I gained a First Class (Hons) BMus. I've been playing the viola for 20 years and, prior to studying at conservatoire level, I passed all ABRSM Violin Grades 1-8.Currently I work for MAPAS (Salford's Music service) and Wigan Music Service. I have a huge range of experience as a soloist, orchestral player and perform regularly with the Cassia String Quartet.I provide private one-to-one violin or viola tuition..

I picked the violin because I liked listening to higher sounds. I felt really great when I got to play the violin because I got to learn a new instrument.One day, I’d like to record my own songs and be in a band. Maybe become a rock star like Ozzy Osbourne!

The benefits of learning the viola is that I get to learn an instrument with my daughter. When I was at school I only learnt the recorder!Learning the viola has given me the chance to play at Sage Gateshead twice, which was amazing. I have also played in the school concerts. I never thought that I would ever play, let alone to do a concert at Sage Gateshead or at school.  It’s even better that I get to share it with Lacey.
liked the sound of it… before I started, I didn’t know how to read music, or what notes were

The deep low notes shook my core, the high notes flitted about like butterflies and fairies. I played with the brass pedals, learning how each affected the strings, and my small fingers tapped at the keys as I experimented with sound. Enchanted by this large and powerful instrument, I wanted to learn how these sounds worked together. I wanted to play the music I heard all around me and imagined making my own songs.
